oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Postcard from Cpl. John Shannon Garrett to Mrs. D. F. Garrett
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Garrett worked in the 90th Aero Squadron repairing, installing, and maintaining the radios in the planes and the radio station. The postcard is address to Mrs. D. F. Garrett in Bemis, Tennessee and was sent from Hempstead, New York.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
